obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (58222)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58222&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Institutes of Food`
  line `Technology, Entrepreneurship and Management Act, 2021.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any reference`
  line `in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming`
  line `into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st October, 2021, vide notification No. S.O. 4036(E), dated 30th September, 2021, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3 (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (58223)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration of certain Institutes as institutions of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58223&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Whereas the objects`
  line `of the Institutes mentioned in the Schedule are such as to make them institutions of national importance, it`
  line `is hereby declared that each such Institute is an institution of national importance.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (58224)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58224&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" in relation to an Institute means the Board of Governors referred to in section 11;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) "corresponding Institute" in relation to an Institute mentioned in column (2) of the Schedule,`
  line `means an Institute as specified in column (3) of the said Schedule;`
  line
  line `(d) "Council" means the Council established under section 28;`
  line
  line `(e) "Director" means the Director of the Institute appointed under section 19;`
  line
  line `(f) "existing Institute" means an Institute mentioned in column (2) of the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(g) "Fund" means the Fund of the Institute to be maintained under section 33;`
  line
  line `(h) "Institute" means the Institute mentioned in column (3) of the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(i) "Member" means a Member of the Board and includes the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(j) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(k) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "Registrar" means the Registrar of the Institute appointed under section 20;`
  line
  line `(m) "Schedule" means the Schedule appended to this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) "Senate" means the Senate of the Institute referred to in section 16;`
  line
  line `(o) "Society" means the existing Institute registered as a Society under the Societies Registration`
  line `Act, 1860 (21 of 1860); and`
  line
  line `(p) "Statutes and Ordinances" in relation to any Institute means, the Statutes and Ordinances of`
  line `that Institute made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (58225)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Incorporation of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58225&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On and from the date of commencement of this Act, each of the`
  line `Institute mentioned in column (3) of the Schedule shall be a body corporate, having perpetual succession`
  line `and a common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of`
  line `property, both movable and immovable, and to contract and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (58226)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Effect of incorporation of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58226&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On and from the date of commencement of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) any reference to an existing Institute in any other law for the time being in force or in any`
  line `contract or other instrument shall be deemed as a reference to the corresponding Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) all properties, movable and immovable, of or belonging to an existing Institute shall vest in`
  line `the corresponding Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) all rights and liabilities of an existing Institute shall be transferred to, and be the rights and`
  line `liabilities of the corresponding Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) every person employed by an existing Institute immediately before such commencement shall`
  line `hold his office or service in the corresponding Institute, with the same tenure, for the same`
  line `remuneration and upon the same terms and conditions and with the same rights and privileges as to`
  line `pension, leave, gratuity, provident fund and other matters as he would have held had this Act not been`
  line `enacted, and shall continue to do so unless and until his employment is terminated or until such`
  line `tenure, remuneration, terms and conditions are duly altered by the Statutes:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the alteration so made is not acceptable to such employee, his employment may`
  line `be terminated by the Institute in accordance with the terms and conditions of the contract with the`
  line `said employee or, if no provision is made therein in this behalf, on payment to him by the Institute, of`
  line `compensation equivalent to three months' remuneration in case of permanent employee and one`
  line `month's remuneration in the case of other employee:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any reference, by whatever form of words, to the Director or Vice-Chancellor, and other officers of an existing Institute under any law for the time being in force, or any`
  line `instrument or other document, shall be construed as a reference to the Director, and other officers of`
  line `the corresponding Institute;`
  line
  line `(e) every person pursuing, before commencement of this Act, any academic or research course in`
  line `an existing Institute, shall be deemed to have migrated and registered with the corresponding`
  line `Institute, on such commencement at the same level of course in the Institute from which such person`
  line `migrated; and`
  line
  line `(f) all suits and other legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or`
  line `against an existing Institute, immediately before the commencement of this Act, shall be continued or`
  line `instituted by or against the corresponding Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (58227)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Powers and functions of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58227&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, each Institute shall`
  line `exercise the following powers and perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to provide for instruction and research in such branches of food science and food technology,`
  line `and any other branches of engineering, technology, science and management as the Institute may`
  line `think fit, and for the advancement of learning and dissemination of knowledge in such branches;`
  line
  line `(b) to hold examinations and grant degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions`
  line `or titles;`
  line
  line `(c) to confer honorary degrees or other distinctions;`
  line
  line `(d) to fix, demand and receive fees and other charges;`
  line
  line `(e) to establish, maintain and manage halls and hostels for the residence of students;`
  line
  line `(f) to supervise and control the discipline of all categories of employees and students of the`
  line `Institute and to make arrangements for promoting their health, general welfare, cultural and corporate`
  line life;
  line
  line `(g) to provide for the maintenance of units of the National Cadet Corps for the students;`
  line
  line `(h) to institute academic and other posts and to make appointments thereto except the Director;`
  line
  line `(i) to deal with any property belonging to or vested in the Institute in such manner as the Institute`
  line `may deem fit for advancing the objects of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(j) to receive gifts, grants, donations or benefactions from the Government and to receive`
  line `bequests, donations and transfers of movable or immovable property from testators, donors or`
  line `transferors, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(k) to co-operate and collaborate with educational or other institutions in any part of the world`
  line `having objects wholly or partly similar to those of the Institute by exchange of teachers and scholars`
  line `and generally in such manner as may be conducive to their common objects;`
  line
  line `(l) to institute and award fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, prizes and medals; and`
  line
  line `(m) to do all such things as may be necessary, incidental or conducive to the attainment of all or`
  line `any of the objects of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), an Institute shall not dispose of in any`
  line `manner any immovable property without the prior approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (58228)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Institutes to be open to all races, creed and classes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58228&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each Institute shall be open to all`
  line `persons irrespective of gender, race, creed, caste or class, and no test or condition shall be imposed as to`
  line `religious belief or profession in admitting or appointing members, students, teachers, officers, employees`
  line `or workers or in any other connection whatsoever.`
  line
  line `(2) No bequest, donation or transfer of any property shall be accepted by any Institute, which in the`
  line `opinion of the Council involves conditions or obligations opposed to the spirit and object of this section.`
  line
  line `(3) The admission to every academic course or programme of study in each Institute shall be based on`
  line `merit, assessed through transparent and reasonable criteria disclosed through its prospectus, prior to the`
  line `commencement of the process of admission by such Institute:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent the Institute from making special`
  line `provisions for the employment or admission of women, persons with disabilities or for persons belonging`
  line `to any socially and educationally backward classes of citizens and, in particular, for the Scheduled Castes`
  line `and the Scheduled Tribes:`
  line
  line `Provided further that each such Institute shall be a Central Educational Institution for the purposes of`
  line `the Central Educational Institutions (Reservation in Admission) Act, 2006 (5 of 2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (58229)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Institutes to be not-for-profit legal entity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58229&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each Institute shall be a not-for-profit legal entity`
  line `and no part of the surplus, if any, in revenue of the Institute, after meeting all expenditures in regard to its`
  line `operations under this Act, shall be invested for any purpose other than for the growth and development of`
  line `the Institute or for conducting research therein.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Institute shall strive to raise funds for self-sufficiency and sustainability.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (58230)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Teaching at Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58230&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `All teaching at each of the Institutes shall be conducted by or in the name`
  line `of the Institute in accordance with the Statutes and Ordinances made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (58231)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Authorities of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58231&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The following shall be the authorities of an Institute, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Board of Governors;`
  line
  line `(b) a Senate; and`
  line
  line `(c) such other authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be the authorities of the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (58232)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Board of Governors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58232&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of Governors of each Institute shall be the principal`
  line `executive body of that Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board of each Institute shall consist of the following Members, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson, from amongst eminent persons distinguished in the field of food industry or`
  line `education or food science or food processing technology or management or such other field, to be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) the Director of the Institute --- Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) the Chairperson of the Food Safety and`
  line `Standards Authority of India or his nominee`
  line `--- Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Director-General of the Indian`
  line `Council of Agricultural Research or his nominee`
  line `--- Member,ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) one representative, not below the rank of`
  line `a Director, of the Ministry or Department of the`
  line `Central Government dealing with Food`
  line `Processing Industries`
  line `--- Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) two representatives having special`
  line `knowledge in the field of food processing`
  line `industry to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government
  line `--- Members;`
  line
  line `(g) one representative from an Indian`
  line `Institute of Management`
  line `--- Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) one representative from an Indian`
  line `Institute of Technology`
  line `--- Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(i) the Dean of Faculty of the Institute, if any --- Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(j) Secretary to the Government of India in`
  line `the Department of Higher Education or his`
  line nominee
  line `--- Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(k) three faculty members of the Institute`
  line `from amongst Professors, Associate Professors`
  line `and Assistant Professors, by rotation of seniority`
  line `--- Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(l) one nominee of the concerned State`
  line `Government not below the rank of a Joint`
  line Secretary
  line `--- Member, ex officio;and`
  line
  line `(m) Registrar of the Institute --- Member-Secretary,ex officio.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall have the power to invite any number of experts, not being members of the`
  line `Board, to attend meetings of the Board, but such invitees shall not be entitled to vote at the meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (58233)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Powers and functions of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58233&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board of each`
  line `Institute shall be responsible for the general superintendence, direction and control of the affairs of the`
  line `Institute and shall exercise all the powers of the Institute not otherwise provided for by this Act, the`
  line `Statutes and the Ordinances, and shall have the power to review the acts of the Senate.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Board of each Institute shall exercise`
  line `the following powers and perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to take decision on questions of policy relating to the administration and working of the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(b) to examine and approve the annual budget estimates of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) to examine and approve the plan for development of the Institute and to identify sources of`
  line `finance for implementation of the plan;`
  line
  line `(d) to establish departments, faculties or schools of studies and initiate programmes or courses of`
  line `study at the Institute;`
  line
  line `(e) to set-up centres of food processing studies and allied areas within the country after approval`
  line `of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(f) to grant degrees, diplomas and other academic distinctions or titles, and to institute and award`
  line `fellowships, scholarships, prizes and medals;`
  line
  line `(g) to confer honorary degrees in such manner as may be specified by the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(h) to grant honorary awards and other distinctions;`
  line
  line `(i) to create academic, administrative, technical and other posts and determine, by Statutes, the`
  line `qualification, classification, terms and conditions of service and method of appointment of such posts;`
  line
  line `(j) to set-up centres of food processing studies and allied areas outside India in accordance with`
  line `the guidelines laid down by the Central Government from time to time and in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the laws for the time being in force in such foreign country;`
  line
  line `(k) to pay, variable pay to the Director of the Institute on the basis of performance objectives as`
  line `may be specified by the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(l) to make, amend and repeal the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(m) to consider and modify or cancel the Ordinances; and`
  line
  line `(n) to exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may be conferred on or`
  line `assigned to it by this Act or the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board may, by Statutes, delegate such powers and`
  line `functions of the Board to the Director as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall conduct an annual review of the performance of the Director, in the context of the`
  line `achievements of objects of the Institute:`
  line
  line `Provided that such review shall include performance review of faculty members of the Institute on`
  line `such parameters, periodicity and terms of reference as may be determined by the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board shall, through an independent agency or group of experts, within a period of three`
  line `years from the date of incorporation of the Institute, and thereafter at least once every three years, evaluate and review the performance of the Institute, including its faculty, on the parameters of long term`
  line `strategy and rolling plans of the Institute and such other parameters as the Board may decide and the`
  line `report of such review shall be placed in public domain.`
  line
  line `(6) The qualifications, experience and the manner of selection of the independent agency or group of`
  line `experts, referred to in sub-section (5), shall be such as may be specified by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(7) The report of the evaluation and review under sub-section (5) shall be submitted by the Board to`
  line `the Central Government along with an action taken report:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may after considering the report, give suggestions to the Board`
  line `for further actions to be taken by it.`
  line
  line `(8) Where in the opinion of the Chairperson or the Director, the situation is so emergent that an`
  line `immediate decision needs to be taken in the interest of the Institute, the Chairperson, in consultation with`
  line `the Director, may issue such orders as may be necessary after recording the grounds for his opinion:`
  line
  line `Provided that such orders shall be submitted for ratification by the Board in the next meeting.`
  line
  line `(9) The Board shall, in exercise of its powers and discharge of its functions under this Act, be`
  line `accountable to the Central Government, and the Central Government may issue directions to the Board in`
  line `public interest on the matters of policy.`
  line
  line `(10) The Board shall have the power to appoint such Committees as it considers necessary for the`
  line `exercise of its powers and performance of its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (58234)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Term of office of, vacancies among, and allowances payable to, Members of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58234&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this section, the term of office of the Chairperson or a Member, other than`
  line `an ex officio Member, shall be for a period of three years from the date of his appointment or nomination.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of an ex officio Member shall continue so long as he holds the office by virtue`
  line `of which he is a member of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, an outgoing Member, other than an ex officio`
  line `Member, shall, unless the Council otherwise directs, continue in office until another person is nominated`
  line `as a Member in his place or until the expiry of six months whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(4) The Members of the Board, other than an ex officio Member, shall be entitled to such allowances,`
  line `as may be provided by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (58235)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Filling of casual vacancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58235&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `When a vacancy occurs in the office of the Chairperson or Member`
  line `whether by reason of removal, resignation, death or otherwise, such vacancy shall be filled within a`
  line `period of six months from the date of such vacancy in accordance with the provisions of section 11.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (58236)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Resignation of Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58236&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson or a Member, other than an ex officio Member,`
  line `may, by notice in writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government, resign his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson or a Member, other than an ex officio Member, shall, unless he is`
  line `permitted by the Central Government to relinquish his office sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of six months from the date of receipt of such notice or until a person duly appointed as his`
  line `successor enters upon his office or until the expiry of his term of office, whichever is the earliest.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (58237)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Senate.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58237&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Senate shall be the principal academic body of the Institute, consisting of the`
  line `following persons, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the Director --- Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) the Registrar --- Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) all full time faculty at the level of`
  line `Professors appointed or recognised as`
  line `such by the Institute for the purpose of`
  line `imparting instructions in the Institute`
  line `--- Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) three persons, not being employees of`
  line `the Institute, to be nominated by the`
  line `Board in consultation with the Director`
  line `from amongst academicians of repute, one`
  line `each from the fields of food science,`
  line `management and food technology`
  line `--- Members; and`
  line
  line `(e) such other members of the staff as`
  line `may be laid down in the Statutes`
  line `--- Members, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of a Member nominated under clause (d) of sub-section (1) shall be two years`
  line `from the date of his nomination.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of an ex officio Member shall continue so long as he holds the office by virtue`
  line `of which he is a Member.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (58238)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Functions of Senate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58238&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances, the`
  line `Senate of an Institute shall have the control and general regulation, and be responsible for the`
  line `maintenance of standards of instruction, education and examination in the Institute and shall exercise such`
  line `other powers and perform such other functions as may be conferred on or assigned to it by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (58239)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Powers and functions of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58239&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall ordinarily preside at the`
  line `meetings of the Board and at the Convocations of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the Chairperson to ensure that the decisions taken by the Board are`
  line implemented.
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may be`
  line `conferred on or assigned to him by this Act or the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (58240)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title Director.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58240&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director shall be appointed by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director shall be the principal academic and executive officer of the Institute and shall be`
  line `responsible for the proper administration of the Institute and for imparting of instruction and maintenance`
  line `of discipline therein.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director shall submit annual reports and accounts to the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The Director shall exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may be`
  line `conferred on or assigned to him by this Act or the Statutes or Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (58241)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title Registrar.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58241&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar of each Institute shall be appointed on such terms and conditions as`
  line `may be laid down by the Statutes and shall be the custodian of the records, common seal, funds of the`
  line `Institute and such other property of the Institute as the Board shall commit to his charge.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall act as the Secretary of the Board, the Senate and such Committees as may be`
  line `specified by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall be responsible to the Director for the proper discharge of his functions.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar shall exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may be`
  line `conferred on or assigned to him by this Act or the Statutes or by the Director.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (58242)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Other authorities and officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58242&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The powers and functions of other authorities and officers,`
  line `other than those mentioned above, shall be such as may be determined by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (58243)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title Appointments.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58243&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `All appointments of the staff of every Institute shall be made in accordance`
  line `with the procedure laid down in the Statutes, by--`
  line
  line `(a) the Board, if the appointment is of the academic staff in the post of Assistant Professor or`
  line `above or if the appointment is of the non-academic staff in any post which is above level 7 in the pay`
  line `matrix; and`
  line
  line `(b) the Director, in any other case.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (58244)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Statutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58244&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for all or any of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the conferment of honorary degrees;`
  line
  line `(b) the formation of departments of teaching;`
  line
  line `(c) the fees to be charged for courses of study in the Institute and for admission to the`
  line `examinations for degrees and diplomas of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) the institution of fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(e) the qualifications, classification, terms and conditions of service and method of appointment`
  line `to academic, administrative, technical and other posts;`
  line
  line `(f) the constitution of pension, insurance and provident funds for the benefit of the officers,`
  line `teachers and other staff of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(g) the constitution, powers and functions of the authorities of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(h) the establishment and maintenance of halls and hostels;`
  line
  line `(i) the conditions for residence of students of the Institute and charging of fees for residence in`
  line `the halls and hostels and other charges;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of filling up the vacancies of Members of the Board;`
  line
  line `(k) the allowances to be paid to the Chairperson and Members of the Board;`
  line
  line `(l) the authentication of the orders and decisions of the Board;`
  line
  line `(m) the financial accountability of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(n) the meetings of the Board, the Senate, or any Committee, the quorum at such meetings and the`
  line `procedure to be followed in the conduct of their business; and`
  line
  line `(o) any other matter which, by this Act, is required to be, or may be, specified by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (58245)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Statutes how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58245&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The first Statutes of each Institute shall be framed by the Council with`
  line `the previous approval of the Central Government and a copy of the same shall be laid as soon as may be`
  line `after they are made before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, from time to time, make new or additional Statutes or may amend or repeal the`
  line `Statutes in the manner hereafter provided in this section.`
  line
  line `(3) Every new Statute or addition to the Statutes or any amendment or repeal of Statute shall require`
  line `the previous approval of the Central Government which may approve it or remit it to the Board for`
  line consideration.
  line
  line `(4) A new Statute or a Statute amending or repealing an existing Statute shall have no validity unless`
  line `it has been approved by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (58246)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title Ordinances.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58246&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the Ordinances of the`
  line `Institute may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of the students to the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) the courses of study to be laid down for all degrees and diplomas of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions under which students shall be admitted to the degree or diploma courses and to`
  line `the examinations of the Institute, and shall be eligible for degrees and diplomas;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions of award of the fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions and mode of appointment and duties of examining bodies, examiners and`
  line moderators;
  line
  line `(f) the conduct of examinations;`
  line
  line `(g) the maintenance of discipline among the students of the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which, by this Act or the Statutes, is to be or may be provided for by the`
  line Ordinances.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (58247)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Ordinances how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58247&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, the Ordinances shall be`
  line `made by the Senate.`
  line
  line `(2) All Ordinances made by the Senate shall have effect from such date as it may direct, but every`
  line `Ordinance so made shall be submitted, as soon as may be after it is made, to the Board and shall be`
  line `considered by the Board at its next meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall have power by resolution to modify or cancel any Ordinance and such Ordinance`
  line `shall from the date of such resolution stand modified accordingly or cancelled, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (58248)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58248&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any dispute arising out of a contract between the Institute and any`
  line `of its employees shall, at the request of the employee concerned or at the instance of the Institute, be`
  line `referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed by the Institute, one member`
  line `nominated by the employee concerned, and an umpire appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Tribunal of Arbitration shall be final, and no suit shall lie in any civil court in`
  line `respect of the matters decided by the said Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall preclude the employee or the Institute, as the case may`
  line `be, from availing the judicial remedies available under articles 32 and 226 of the Constitution.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal of Arbitration shall have power to regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in any law for the time being in force relating to arbitration shall apply to arbitrations`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (58249)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Establishment of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58249&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify in this behalf, there shall be established a central body to be called the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall consist of the following members, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the Minister in-charge of Food`
  line `Processing Industries, Central Government`
  line `--- Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) the Minister of the State for Food`
  line `Processing Industries, Central Government`
  line `--- member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) Chairperson, Food Safety and Standards`
  line `Authority of India`
  line `--- member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Secretary to the Government of India`
  line `in-charge of the Ministry or Department of`
  line `the Central Government dealing with`
  line Finance
  line `--- member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Chief Executive Officer, National`
  line `Institution for Transforming India`
  line `--- member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) the Secretary to the Government of India`
  line `in-charge of the Ministry or Department of`
  line `the Central Government dealing with Higher`
  line Education
  line `---member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) three representatives of eminence from`
  line `Food Processing Industry to be nominated by`
  line `the Chairperson of the Council`
  line `--- members;`
  line
  line `(h) three eminent academicians known for`
  line `their contribution in the field of food`
  line `processing, to be nominated by the`
  line `Chairperson of the Council`
  line `--- members;`
  line .
  line `(i) three Members of Parliament, of whom`
  line `two shall be elected by the House of the`
  line `People and one by the Council of States`
  line `--- members:`
  line .
  line
  line `Provided that the office of member of the Council shall not disqualify its holder for being chosen as`
  line `or for being a Member of either House of Parliament;`
  line
  line `(j) the Secretary to the Government of India`
  line `in-charge of the Ministry of the Central`
  line `Government dealing with Food Processing`
  line Industries
  line `--- Member-Secretary, ex officio;`
  line .
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by order, designate one amongst the members as Vice-chairperson`
  line `to the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (58250)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Term of office of, vacancies among, and allowances payable to members of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58250&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this section, the term of office of a member of the Council, other than an`
  line `ex officio member, shall be for a period of three years from the date of his nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that the term of member referred to in clause (i) of sub-section (2) of section 28 shall come`
  line `to an end as soon as the member becomes a Minister or Minister of State or Deputy Minister or the`
  line `Speaker or the Deputy Speaker of the House of the people or the Deputy Chairman of the Council of`
  line `States or ceases to be a Member of the House from which he was elected.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of an ex officio member shall continue so long as he holds the office by virtue`
  line `of which he is a member.`
  line
  line `(3) The members of the Council referred to in clauses (g) and (h) of sub-section (2) of section 28 shall`
  line `hold office during the pleasure of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The vacancy of a member of the Council, other than an ex officio member, shall be filled up in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office of a member nominated to fill a casual vacancy shall continue for the`
  line `remainder of the term of the member in whose place he has been so nominated.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, an outgoing member, other than an ex officio`
  line `member, shall, unless the Central Government otherwise directs, continue in office until another person is`
  line `nominated as a member in his place or until the expiry of six months whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(7) The members of the Council, other than ex officio members, shall be paid such travelling and`
  line `other allowances as may be provided by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(8) A member of the Council other than an ex officio member may be removed from his office by the`
  line `Central Government in such circumstances and manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (58251)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Functions of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58251&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the general function of the Council to co-ordinate the`
  line `activities of all the Institutes and it shall facilitate the sharing of experiences, ideas and concerns with a`
  line `view to enhance the performance of the Institutes.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Council shall perform the following`
  line `functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to lay down broader policy framework for the functioning of the Institutes;`
  line
  line `(b) to recommend to the Central Government, the institution of scholarships including for`
  line `research and for the benefit of students belonging to the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and`
  line `other socially and educationally backward classes of citizens;`
  line
  line `(c) to deliberate on such matters of common interest to Institutes as may be referred to it by an`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(d) to promote necessary coordination and co-operation in the working of the Institutes;`
  line
  line `(e) to review the achievement of policy objectives; and`
  line
  line `(f) to perform such other functions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (58252)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Meetings of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58252&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The Council shall meet at such time and place and follow such procedure`
  line `in its meetings (including quorum at such meetings) as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (58253)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58253&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of enabling the Institutes to discharge their`
  line `functions efficiently under this Act, the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to each of the Institute in each financial year such sums of money`
  line `and in such manner as it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (58254)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Fund of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58254&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each Institute shall maintain a Fund to which shall be credited,--`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys provided by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees and other charges received by the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) all moneys received by the Institute by way of grants, gifts, donations, benefactions, bequests`
  line `or transfers; and`
  line
  line `(d) all moneys received by the Institute in any other manner or from any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys credited to the Fund of each Institute shall be deposited in such banks or invested in`
  line `such manner as the Institute may, with the approval of the Board, decide.`
  line
  line `(3) The Fund of each Institute shall be applied towards meeting the expenses of the Institute including`
  line `expenses incurred in the exercise of its powers and discharge of its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (58255)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58255&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each Institute shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts including the balance sheet in such form and manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of each Institute shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be payable by the Institute to the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of any Institute shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of the Government accounts, and, in particular shall have the right to demand the production of`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the offices of the`
  line Institute.
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of each Institute as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament in accordance with such procedure as may be laid down by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (58256)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Pension, insurance and provident funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58256&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each Institute shall constitute for the benefit of`
  line `its employees, including the Director, in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be specified`
  line `by the Statutes, such pension, insurance and provident funds as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the provident fund referred to in sub-section (1) has been constituted, the Central`
  line `Government may declare that the provision of the Provident Funds Act, 1925 (19 of 1925) shall apply to`
  line `such fund as if it were a Government Provident Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (58257)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Acts and proceedings not to be invalidate by vacancies, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58257&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `No act of the Council, or any`
  line `Institute, or Board, or Senate or any other Committee set up under this Act or the Statutes shall be invalid`
  line `merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or defect in, the constitution thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the nomination or appointment of a person acting as member thereof; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in its procedure not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (58258)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58258&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Chairperson or Members of the Board, Senate or Council or any officer or employee of the`
  line `Institute for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (58259)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58259&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry`
  line `out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of filling up the vacancy under sub-section (4) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(b) the circumstances and the manner in which a member of the Council may be removed from`
  line `his office under sub-section (8) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(c) the other functions of the Council under clause (f) of sub-section (2) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(d) the time and place of meeting of the Council, its quorum and the procedure for conducting`
  line `business therein under section 31;`
  line
  line `(e) the form and manner in which the annual statement of accounts including the balance sheet`
  line `shall be prepared under sub-section (1) of section 34; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (58263)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Rules, Statutes and Ordinances to be published in Official Gazette and to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58263&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every rule, every Statute and every Ordinance made under this Act shall be published`
  line `in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule, every Statute and every Ordinance made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be, after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule, Statute or Ordinance or both Houses agree that the rule, Statute or`
  line `Ordinance should not be made, the rule, Statute or Ordinance shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule, Statute`
  line `or Ordinance.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (58261)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58261&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for`
  line `removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (58262)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344&sectionId=58262&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00001_202119_1633427623344
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Board of Governors of an Institute functioning as such immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall continue to function until a new Board is constituted for that Institute`
  line `under this Act, but on the constitution of a new Board under this Act, the members of the existing`
  line `Board holding office before such constitution shall cease to hold office;`
  line
  line `(b) until the first Statutes and Ordinances are made under this Act, the Statutes and Ordinances of`
  line `the existing Institutes, as in force immediately before the commencement of this Act, shall continue to`
  line `apply to the corresponding Institutes in so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
